Enum MemoryPolicy

  • java.lang.Object

    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MemoryPolicy>

    public enum MemoryPolicy
extends java.lang.Enum<MemoryPolicy>
    Designates the policy to use when dealing with memory cache.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      NO_CACHE
      Skips memory cache lookup when processing a request.
      NO_STORE
      Skips storing the final result into memory cache.

      • NO_CACHE

        public static final MemoryPolicy NO_CACHE
        Skips memory cache lookup when processing a request.

      • NO_STORE

        public static final MemoryPolicy NO_STORE
        Skips storing the final result into memory cache. Useful for one-off requests to avoid evicting other bitmaps from the cache.
